description.narrative: Originally scoped as a mini-hydro plant development project in 2013 at the request of GoPNG, the ‘Enga Electrification Project’ was subsequently re-scoped in 2018 following a cost review which resulted in the GoPNG deciding to put the hydro component on hold and invest in extension of the main grid and connecting households instead. This activity is jointly funded with Australia and will provide a distribution network and household connections in the Tsak Valley.
